{"type":"message","id":"6d44fd6e","parentId":"a9d194dc","timestamp":"2026-06-30T22:30:56.511Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the log output, the service started successfully:\n1. Server process started (PID 42524)\n2. Waiting for application startup\n3. Some modules not found (src.stream, src.calibration, src.database) - these are expected to be optional\n4. PTZDeviceController initialized\n5. ConfigManager initialized with devices_dir\n6. SADP DLLs loaded\n7. Device discovered: MAC=24-0f-9b-76-41-93, IP=192.168.5.72\n\nHowever, the process was killed with SIGKILL. This is unusual. Let me check if there was a timeout or if the service crashed. The log shows the service was running and discovering devices, so it seems like it was working.\n\nI need to:\n1. Check if the service is still running on port 10280\n2. If not, restart it in the background\n3. Then run the e2e test\n\nLet me first check if the port is listening and the service is accessible.\n服务启动成功！看到：\n- PTZDeviceController 初始化完成\n- ConfigManager 初始化成功\n- SADP DLL 加载完成\n- 发现设备: MAC=24-0f-9b-76-41-93, IP=192.168.5.72\n\n但进程被 SIGKILL 终止了。让我在后台重新启动服务，然后运行测试：\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_1f1291c768d24e108d650be4","name":"exec","arguments":{"background":true,"command":"cd astrohub; python -m src.main.main --headless 2>&1","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":2127,"output":409,"cacheRead":149658,"cacheWrite":172,"totalTokens":152366,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782858644951,"responseId":"msg_d2aea3ae-3126-45a3-8fbb-008fc08ce48e"}}
