{"type":"message","id":"bfeb7c1e","parentId":"32d43a6c","timestamp":"2026-06-30T23:05:23.011Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The backup directory's tools folder appears to be empty as well. Let me understand what's happening:\n\n1. The user wants to continue\n2. I'm trying to find the e2e test script to run\n3. The tools/ directory in both the main astrohub folder and the backup folder are empty\n\nThis is strange because earlier in the conversation, I saw that `tools/e2e_v7120_test.py` was deleted as an orphan file (13750 bytes). But now the backup doesn't seem to have it either.\n\nLet me check if there are any other test scripts or if maybe the user wants me to create a simple test or skip the test entirely.\n\nActually, looking at the system message, the user just said \"继续\" (continue) after my summary report. The service is running fine and all APIs are returning 200 OK. The cleanup and refactoring has been completed successfully.\n\nSince the e2e test script was deleted and is not in the backup, I have a few options:\n1. Create a simple test script to verify the service is working\n2. Use curl/PowerShell to test the APIs manually\n3. Report to the user that the test script was deleted during cleanup\n\nGiven the constraints, let me do a manual API test to verify the service is working correctly. I'll use PowerShell to call the main APIs and verify they return 200 OK.\n\nThis will serve as a basic E2E test:\n1. Health check\n2. Device list\n3. PTZ position\n4. WebSocket connection\n\nLet me perform these tests.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"老板说\"继续\"。发现测试脚本在清理时被删除且备份中没有。让我直接用 PowerShell 进行 API 端点测试作为 E2E 验证：\n\n## v8.01 E2E 测试（手动验证）"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_95656d15de44451c97721069","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$baseUrl = \"http://localhost:10280/api/v1\"\n$results = @()\n\n# Test 1: Health check\ntry { \n    $r = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri \"$baseUrl/../health\" -UseBasicParsing -TimeoutSec 5\n    $results += \"✅ Health: $($r.StatusCode)\"\n} catch { \n    $results += \"❌ Health: $($_.Exception.Message)\" \n}\n\n# Test 2: Devices list\ntry { \n    $r = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri \"$baseUrl/devices\" -UseBasicParsing -TimeoutSec 5\n    $results += \"✅ Devices: $($r.StatusCode)\"\n} catch { \n    $results += \"❌ Devices: $($_.Exception.Message)\" \n}\n\n# Test 3: PTZ Position\ntry { \n    $r = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri \"$baseUrl/ptz/192.168.5.72/position\" -UseBasicParsing -TimeoutSec 5\n    $results += \"✅ PTZ Position: $($r.StatusCode)\"\n} catch { \n    $results += \"❌ PTZ Position: $($_.Exception.Message)\" \n}\n\n# Test 4: Image settings\ntry { \n    $r = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri \"$baseUrl/ptz/192.168.5.72/image/iris\" -UseBasicParsing -TimeoutSec 5\n    $results += \"✅ Image Iris: $($r.StatusCode)\"\n} catch { \n    $results += \"❌ Image Iris: $($_.Exception.Message)\" \n}\n\n# Test 5: Version\ntry { \n    $r = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri \"$baseUrl/../version\" -UseBasicParsing -TimeoutSec 5\n    $v = $r.Content | ConvertFrom-Json\n    $results += \"✅ Version: $($v.version)\"\n} catch { \n    $results += \"❌ Version: $($_.Exception.Message)\" \n}\n\n$results | ForEach-Object { Write-Host $_ }","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":122643,"output":820,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":123463,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782860693985,"responseId":"cht000d6660@dx19f1ac756802872503"}}
