{"type":"message","id":"43317418","parentId":"f9569818","timestamp":"2026-06-30T23:14:39.170Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, the second edit failed because the text was already changed. Good. Now the main issue is the CSS selector syntax error. The Playwright selectors with `has-text()` mixed with regular CSS selectors are causing errors. I need to rewrite the entire script to use simpler, more reliable selectors.\n\nLooking at the error messages:\n```\nLocator.count: Unexpected token \"=\" while parsing css selector \"button:has-text(\"设备\"), [data-page=\"devices\"], .nav-btn:has-text(\"设备\"), text=\"设备\"\". Did you mean to CSS.escape it?\n```\n\nThe problem is that Playwright's `has-text()` pseudo-class can't be used in standard CSS selectors like this. I need to use Playwright's locator API properly, or use simpler CSS selectors.\n\nLet me rewrite the script to:\n1. Use simpler CSS selectors without `has-text()` mixed with other selectors\n2. Use Playwright's text selector properly\n3. Test against the actual web UI structure\n\nActually, looking at the test results so far:\n- Page loads: PASS\n- Title check: PASS\n- API endpoints: ALL PASS (6/6)\n\nThe issue is just the UI navigation selectors. Let me simplify them to use basic CSS classes and text content without the complex `has-text()` pseudo-classes.\n\nActually, let me check the actual HTML structure of the navigation to write better selectors.\n主要问题是 CSS 选择器语法。让我重写脚本使用更可靠的选择器。先检查实际的 HTML 结构：\n\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_ac85a8ce7f674881b7a64755","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd astrohub; python -c \"\nfrom playwright.async_api import async_playwright\nimport asyncio\n\nasync def check():\n    async with async_playwright() as pw:\n        browser = await pw.chromium.launch(headless=True)\n        page = await browser.new_page()\n        await page.goto('http://127.0.0.1:10280')\n        await page.wait_for_load_state('networkidle')\n        \n        # Get navigation structure\n        nav_html = await page.evaluate('''() => {\n            const nav = document.querySelector('nav, .nav, .sidebar, [class*=\\\"nav\\\"]');\n            if (nav) return nav.outerHTML.substring(0, 2000);\n            // fallback: get all buttons and links\n            const buttons = document.querySelectorAll('button, a');\n            return Array.from(buttons).slice(0, 20).map(b => b.outerHTML.substring(0, 200)).join('\\n');\n        }''')\n        print('Navigation structure:')\n        print(nav_html[:3000])\n        \n        await browser.close()\n\nasyncio.run(check())\n\" 2>&1","timeout":30,"workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":2487,"output":637,"cacheRead":192928,"cacheWrite":758,"totalTokens":196810,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782861262686,"responseId":"msg_66384a04-1e04-4f50-89be-59546be537c2"}}
