{"type":"message","id":"2829d526","parentId":"6e425e1e","timestamp":"2026-06-30T23:41:56.463Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue with the JavaScript code is likely the escaping of the backslash in the string. When Python passes the string to JavaScript, the `\\\\n` becomes a literal `\\n` which JavaScript interprets as a newline character in a string. But there might be other issues with the escaping.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach. Instead of trying to get the HTML structure through page.evaluate(), let me use a much simpler approach: just get the text content of buttons and links, which will tell us what navigation items exist.\n\nActually, the error \"SyntaxError: Invalid or unexpected token\" suggests that the JavaScript code being passed has syntax errors. Let me use a much simpler JavaScript expression that avoids any potential escaping issues.\n\nThe problem might be that the triple-quoted Python string is not being properly converted to JavaScript. When Python reads `\"\"\"() => {...\"\"\"`, it's creating a string that starts with `() => {`, which is valid JavaScript. But the issue might be with the newline characters or other special characters in the string.\n\nLet me write a completely new, simpler script that avoids these issues entirely.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"JavaScript 引号转义问题。让我用完全不同的方式：直接读取 HTML 文件检查导航结构。\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_187e43929a634607b0906a16","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content astrohub/src/web/index.html -Head 100 | Select-String -Pattern \"nav|button|sidebar|menu|page\" -Context 1,1 | Select-Object -First 30","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":2916,"output":353,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":169957,"totalTokens":173226,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timest