{"type":"message","id":"70469667","parentId":"2067c4eb","timestamp":"2026-07-01T00:25:49.917Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking why the gateway column in the device management page is not displaying correctly. I've already checked the API response and can see that the gateway field is empty (\"gateway\": \"\"). \n\nLet me check:\n1. What the API returns - I can see gateway is empty\n2. What the frontend expects - need to check the devices.html table structure\n3. What the backend is returning - need to check the router.py code\n\nFrom the API response, I can see:\n- The device has \"gateway\": \"\" (empty string)\n- This means the backend is not getting/persisting the gateway value properly\n\nI need to:\n1. Check the backend code to see how gateway is being stored/retrieved\n2. Check if this is a recent regression from the v8.01 changes\n3. Find where the gateway data should be coming from\n\nLet me check the device data storage and API response logic.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"API 返回的 gateway 是空字符串。让我检查后端的数据存储和 API 逻辑：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_2e9ea4169bed41d5b03643dc","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory\\astrohub\\data\\devices\\240f9b764193\\info.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":7260,"output":277,"cacheRead":216521,"cacheWrite":3879,"totalTokens":227937,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782865538203,"responseId":"msg_be4abe8e-4ad9-4280-976c-9a811af1d429"}}
