{"type":"message","id":"5f6255ae","parentId":"10dc046f","timestamp":"2026-07-01T00:26:56.894Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The SADP callback shows: \"ADD, MAC=24-0f-9b-76-41-93, IP=192.168.5.72\" but doesn't show gateway in the log message.\n\nLet me check the actual SADP callback logging to see if gateway is included in the callback. Looking at the callback code, the gateway should be set on the device object.\n\nThe real question is: is this a regression from v8.01 changes, or was the gateway always empty?\n\nLet me check the git diff for router.py to see if we changed anything related to gateway handling. Actually, I remember that in the v8.01 cleanup, we may have removed some code that was responsible for merging SADP data with stored device info.\n","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"The SADP callback shows it found the device but didn't log gateway. Let me check if the gateway was available in the SADP callback data by looking at the callback logging:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_5f7b3a326e5a4cda8f3cd5e4","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd astrohub; Select-String -Path \"src\\core\\sadp_discovery.py\" -Pattern \"callback|ADD|UPDATE\" -Context 5,5 | Select-Object -First 60","workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":6502,"output":304,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":117188,"totalTokens":123994,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782865599764,"responseId":"msg_4afa7641-378d-42cb-a2fa-8e6036f8d34d"}}
