{"type":"message","id":"a1bc62e5","parentId":"f0bd3f7e","timestamp":"2026-07-01T00:29:30.855Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see. Line 819 in sadp_discovery.py sets:\n```python\ndevice.gateway = decode(c_info.szIPv4Gateway)\n```\n\nAnd lines in router.py get gateway from sadp data:\n```python\n\"gateway\": sadp.get(\"gateway\", \"\")\n```\n\nThe problem is that if SADP doesn't broadcast gateway data (device limitation), then the gateway field will be empty.\n\nBut the user says \"又不能正常显示了\" - it was working before. So either:\n1. There was code that was fetching gateway via ISAPI that got removed in v8.01\n2. The SADP was working before and broke with v8.01\n\nLet me check if there's any ISAPI endpoint that can fetch the device's network settings including gateway. If there is, we should use that instead.\n\nActually, the device's network configuration (including gateway) can be fetched via ISAPI endpoint:\n- `/ISAPI/System/network` or `/ISAPI/System/Network`\n\nThis endpoint returns device network settings. This should be called when fetching device info.\n\nBut wait, the current code structure suggests that the gateway should come from SADP, not ISAPI. The SADP SDK is already connected and discovering devices, so it should have access to all device information including gateway.\n\nThe real issue might be:\n1. The device itself is not broadcasting gateway via SADP (some device models don't do this)\n2. The gateway data was never persisted to info.json when the device was first added\n\nLet me check if there's a v7.122 fix that was handling this. The user mentioned v7.122 \"前端三修复\" including something that might have fixed the gateway issue.\n\nActually, looking back at the conversation, I see that v7.122 was about frontend fixes, not backend. The column order was changed but the data source remained SADP.\n\nSo the real question is: was gateway data ever working before?\n\nIf the device always had empty gateway in SADP, then it was never working. But if it WAS working, then something changed.\n\nLet me check if there's any code that was getting gateway from ISAPI that might have been removed in v8.01.\n\nActually, let me just directly troubleshoot the current issue. The API is returning gateway=\"\", so:\n1. Either SADP returned empty\n2. Or the data flow is broken\n\nLet me check if the SADP callback is actually getting gateway data by adding some temporary debug logging or checking the actual device info.\n\nActually, I should check what IP address is actually解决这个问题。网关为空的根本原因现在清楚了：\n\n**SADP 回调中 gateway 字段确实被设置了（第819行），问题在于设备不广播网关**。解决方法：获取设备的网络设置（包含网关）。\n\n从日志和代码可知：后端 API 调用 SADP.get(\"gateway\")，但 ROI 没广播网关 → 网关始终为空。\n\nAFAIK 可能的解决方案：\n1. 通过 ISAPI 的 `/ISAPI/System/network` 端点获取设备的真实网关\n2. 接受只能显示 IP/subnet，网关显示未知\n\n让我检查是否有可用的 ISAPI 端点获取网关：","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bae319955d6745abbb08983f","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://192.168.5.72/ISAPI/System/network 2>&1 | python -m json.tool 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 60","timeout":10,"workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":120439,"output":755,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":121194,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782865683880,"responseId":"cht000df808@dx19f1b136ecc2872503"}}
