{"type":"message","id":"f5000397","parentId":"1b6e96b6","timestamp":"2026-07-01T00:31:00.330Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me understand what's happening. The user is asking why the gateway field in the device management page is not displaying correctly anymore. \n\nI've already identified:\n1. The API returns `gateway: \"\"` (empty string)\n2. The device info.json doesn't have a gateway field\n3. SADP callback structure has `szIPv4Gateway` field but the callback log only prints MAC and IP, not gateway\n\nNow I'm trying to check if there was old code that was getting the gateway that was deleted. The backup file ptz_manager.py doesn't exist in that path.\n\nLet me think about the root cause:\n- The device info.json doesn't have gateway stored\n- The API returns empty gateway from SADP live data\n- The SADP callback should be getting gateway but it's not being stored or returned\n\nThe issue is likely:\n1. SADP callback receives gateway but it's not being persisted to info.json when device is first added\n2. When refresh_devices() is called, it tries to merge live SADP data but if the device doesn't broadcast gateway via SADP, it stays empty\n\nLet me check if there's code that fetches gateway from the device via ISAPI or other means. The device should know its gateway if it's connected to the network.\n\nActually, looking back at the conversation, the user said \"又不能正常显示了\" which means \"cannot display correctly AGAIN\" - this suggests it was working before and broke again.\n\nLet me check what changed in v8.01 that might have broken gateway display. The git diff showed many changes including deletion of ptz_manager.py.\n\nLet me check if there's code in router.py or ptz_controller.py that was responsible for getting gateway data.\nLet me check if there was code in router.py or ptz_controller.py that was fetching gateway:"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,