oundation for UPnP networking is IP addressing. Whe n a device is connected to the\r\nnetwork for the first time, its Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol (DHCP) client will\r\nor DNS forwarding, then it should use this domain name for the following network\r\noperations; if the network is unmanaged and no DHCP server is found, the device must\r\n\r\n=== �� 28 ҳ ===\r\n[9][10], and use this IP address for the following network operations.\r\nOnce given an IP address, the Discovery process will be executed in UPnP networking."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":945,"aggregated":"=== �� 2 ҳ ===\r\n/ISAPI/System/Network/SIP/<ID\r\nD/ISAPI/System/Network /EZVIZ\r\n\r\n=== �� 3 ҳ ===\r\n/ISAPI/System/Network/WirelessDia\r\nUpdate the <NetworkCap >\r\n\r\n=== �� 7 ҳ ===\r\n8.2 /ISAPI/System/Network  ................................ ................................ ................................ .. 33\r\n8.2.1  /ISAPI/System/Network/capabilities ................................ ...........................  34\r\n8.2.2  /ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces  ................................ .............................  34\r\n8.2.3  /ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces/<ID>  ................................ ...................  35\r\n8.2.4  /ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces/<ID>/ipAddress  ................................  36\r\n8.2.5  /ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces/<ID>/wireless  ................................ .... 37\r\n8.2.6  /ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces/<ID>/wireless/accessPointList  ....... 39\r\n8.2.7  /ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces/<ID>/wireless/accessPointList/<ID>  .\r\n8.2.8  /ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces/<ID>/discovery  ................................ . 40\r\n8.2.9  /ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces/<ID>/Link  ................................ ...........  41\r\n8.2.11  /ISAP I/System/Network/interfaces/<ID>/WPS  ................................ .........  43\r\n8.2.12  /ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces/ID/WPS/AutoConnect  ............