....... ........  73\r\n8.2.51  /ISAPI/System/Network/qos/cos  ................................ ................................  73\r\n8.2.52  /ISAPI/System/Network/qos/cos/<ID>  ................................ .......................  74\r\n8.2.53  /ISAPI/System/Network/qos/dscp  ................................ ..............................  75\r\n8.2.54  /ISAPI/System/Network/qos/dscp/<ID> ................................ .....................  76\r\n8.2.55  /ISAPI/System/Network/telnetd  ................................ ................................ .. 77\r\n8.2.56  /ISAPI/System/Network/SIP  ................................ ................................ ........  77\r\n8.2.57  /ISAPI/System/Network/SIP/<ID>  ................................ ..............................  78\r\n8.2.58  /ISAPI/System/Network/SIP/<ID>/SIPInfo  ................................ ................  79\r\n8.2.59  /ISAPI/System/Network/EZVIZ  ................................ ................................ ..... 80\r\n8.2.60  /ISAPI/System/Network/pingtest  ................................ ................................ .... 81\r\n8.2.61  /ISAPI/System/Network/ssh ................................ ................................ ............  81\r\n8.2.62  /ISAPI/System/Network/Ehome  ................................ ................................ ..... 82\r\n\r\n=== �� 14 ҳ ===\r\narchitecture makes networking simple and easy ��, 2008 -12-09. Retrieved on\r\ndevice architecture makes networking simple and easy ��, 2008 -12-10. Retrieved\r\nInteroperability for IP -based Network Devices ��, 2009 -02-05. Retrieved on\r\n\r\n=== �� 17 ҳ ===\r\nNetwork  Configure network interfaces.  8.2\r\n\r\n=== �� 18 ҳ ===\r\nThe URL scheme is used to locate device resources  via a specific protocol in the network.\r\n\r\n=== �� 27 ҳ ===\r\nthemselves. A UPnP compatible device will automatically announce its network address,\r\nsupported devices and services types when connected to a network, and therefore\r\nThe UPnP architecture supports zero -configuration networking, and the device can\r\ndynamically join a network, obtain IP address, announce its name, convey its capabilities\r\nDNS servers are optional and are only used if they are available on the network. D evices\r\ncan leave the network automatically without leaving any unwanted status information\r\nThe foundation for UPnP networking is IP addressing. Whe n a device is connected to the\r\nnetwork for the first time, its Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol (DHCP) client will\r\nor DNS forwarding, then it should use this domain name for the following network\r\noperations; if the network is unmanaged and no DHCP server is found, the device must\r\n\r\n=== �� 28 ҳ ===\r\n[9][10], and use this IP address for the following network operations.\r\nOnce given an IP address, the Discovery process will be executed in UPnP networking.","cwd":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782866351455}}
{"type":"message","id":"fc0a4923","parentId":"51f413a0","timestamp":"2026-07-01T00:39:27.562Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"From the PDF table of contents, I found the key endpoints:\n\n- **8.2.2** `/ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces` - List all network interfaces\n- **8.2.3** `/ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces/<ID>` - Get specific interface details (IP, subnet, gateway)\n- **8.2.4** `/ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces/<ID>/ipAddress` - Get IP address specifically\n\nSo the correct approach is:\n1. GET `/ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces` to list interfaces\n2. GET `/ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces/1` to get interface 1 details including gateway\n\nLet me extract the actual XML structure for these endpoints by reading pages 34-36 (which should contain the details for 8.2.2 and 8.2.3).\n\nKey insight from the documentation:\n- The base endpoint is `/ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces`\n- Each interface has an ID (typically 1 for the main interface)\n- The detailed interface endpoint `/ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces/1` returns IP, subnet, gateway info\n\nLet me get the actual XML response format from pages 34-36.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"找到关键端点了！根据文档目录：\n- `8.2.2` `/ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces` - 列出所有网络接口\n- `8.2.3` `/ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces/<ID>` - 获取指定接口详情（含网关）\n\n让我提取第34-36页的具体XML结构：\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_c4287c4a56b84ae0ae67784b","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd astrohub; python -c \"\nimport PyPDF2\n\nwith open('ISAPI_doc.pdf', 'rb') as f:\n    reader = PyPDF2.PdfReader(f)\n    \n    # 第34-36页包含 /ISAPI/System/Network/interfaces 的详细定义\n    for page_num in [34, 35, 36]:\n        text = reader.pages[page_num-1].extract_text()\n        print(f'=== 第 {page_num} 页 ===')\n        print(text[:2000])  # 每页前2000字符\n        print()\n\" 2>&1","timeout":60,"workdir":"C:\\Users\\admin\\.openclaw\\agents\\dev-factory"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","