{"type":"message","id":"2914ad41","parentId":"757c1b13","timestamp":"2026-07-01T04:16:59.791Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK I can see the issue now. The first edit already changed \"控制台\" to \"主控台\" in the text, but the comments and log messages still say \"控制台页面\" which should be \"主控台页面\".\n\nBut the real issue is simpler - the `has-text()` selector is not the problem. The problem is that `has-text()` is a valid Playwright CSS selector, but when combined with other selectors like `text=\"xxx\"` it breaks. Since we already removed the `text=\"xxx\"` parts, the remaining `has-text()` selectors should work.\n\nHowever, looking at the error from the test run:\n```\nLocator.count: Unexpected token \"=\" while parsing css selector \"button:has-text(\"控制台\"), [data-page=\"console\"], text=\"控制台\", text=\"实时\", text=\"播放\", text=\"监控\"\"\n```\n\nThis error was from BEFORE the first edit. After the first edit, the selector was changed to just `button:has-text(\"主控台\"), [data-page=\"console\"]` which should work fine.\n\nWait, but the first edit DID succeed for 5 blocks. Let me check if the test was re-run after the edit.\n\nActually, looking at the output from the last test run, I see:\n```\n[FAIL] [控制台页面] 导航失败: ...\n```\nThis says \"控制台页面\" which means the edit to change the log message wasn't applied.\n\nBut wait, the error in the log says:\n```\nbutton:has-text(\"控制台\"), [data-page=\"console\"], text=\"控制台\", text=\"实时\", text=\"播放\", text=\"监控\"\n```\n\nBut after my edit, it should say:\n```\nbutton:has-text(\"主控台\"), [data-page=\"console\"]\n```\n\nThis means either:\n1. The edit didn't actually work for this specific block\n2. Or the test was run before the edit was saved\n\nLooking at the edit result: \"Successfully replaced 5 block(s)\" - so the edit did work. But the test was probably run from a cached/buffered version.\n\nLet me just run the test again with the updated script. The current script has the correct selectors.\n\nActually wait, let me re-read the error message from the test output:\n```\n[FAIL] [控制台页面] 导航失败: Locator.count: Unexpected token \"=\" while parsing css selector \"button:has-text(\"控制台\"), [data-page=\"console\"], text=\"控制台\", text=\"实时\", text=\"播放\", text=\"监控\"\"\n```\n\nThis still shows \"控制台\" not \"主控台\". So either the edit didn't apply to this specific instance, or the file was overwritten.\n\nHmm, but the first edit was:\n```python\n\"console_btn = page.locator('button:has-text(\\\"主控台\\\"), [data-page=\\\"console\\\"]').first\"\n```\n\nSo after the edit, the line should be `button:has-text(\"主控台\")` not `button:has-text(\"控制台\")`.\n\nBut the test output shows \"控制台\" still. This is confusing.\n\nActually, looking more carefully, there are TWO console_btn definitions:\n1. Line 121 - in test_wasm_playback_and_stream()\n2. Line 273 - in test_isapi_image_controls()\n\nThe first edit changed line 121 but might have missed line 273. Let me check.\n\nLooking at the edit:\n```\n{\"newText\": \"console_btn = page.locator('button:has-text(\\\"主控台\\\"), [data-page=\\\"console\\\"]').first\", \"oldText\": \"console_btn = page.locator('button:has-text(\\\"控制台\\\"), [data-page=\\\"console\\\"], text=\\\"控制台\\\", text=\\\"实时\\\", text=\\\"播放\\\", text=\\\"监控\\\"').first\"}\n```\n\nThis only matches line 121 (which has `text=\"实时\", text=\"播放\", text=\"监控\"`). Line 273 has different text (`text=\"控制台\"` only) so it didn't match.\n\nLet me check what line 273 looks like now.\n\nActually, wait - the second edit block in the first call was:\n```\n{\"newText\": \"console_btn = page.locator('button:has-text(\\\"主控台\\\"), [data-page=\\\"console\\\"]').first\", \"oldText\": \"console_btn = page.locator('button:has-text(\\\"控制台\\\"), [data-page=\\\"console\\\"], text=\\\"控制台\\\"').first\"}\n```\n\nThis should match line 273. And the first block should match line 121. Both use `text=\"控制台\"` so they should match.\n\nBut looking at the edit result: \"Successfully replaced 5 block(s)\" - so all 5 blocks were replaced.\n\nLet me look at the test output more carefully. The test output says:\n```\n[FAIL] [控制台页面] 导航失败: ... \"button:has-text(\"控制台\"), [data-page=\"console\"], text=\"控制台\", text=\"实时\", text=\"播放\", text=\"监控\"\"\n```\n\nBut after my edit, this line should be `button:has-text(\"主控台\"), [data-page=\"console\"]`.\n\nSo either:\n1. The file wasn't properly saved\n2. Or there's a cache issue\n3. Or the test output is from before the edit was applied\n\nLet me just read the current file content to verify, then run the test again.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"让我直接读取文件确认当前内容，然后运行测试：\n\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_dlpd2ld7cc29dcf1vouvgh85","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Path \"astrohub/tools/e2e_v801_full.py\" -Pattern 'has-text|data-page' | Select-Object LineNumber, Line"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"HP","model":"qwen-3.7-max","usage":{"input":142924,"output":1236,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":144160,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782879379677,"responseId":"cht000da130@dx19f1be485fd29c2503"}}
